ists, and their teams.  Reviewing and improving related internal controls and assisting with ensuring compliance with internal controls, PSAB accounting guidelines, CAMH policies, CICA Handbook standards, and granting agency regulatory requirements.  Developing additional analysis and reporting on a regular or ad-hoc basis. || Key Responsibilities: | Senior Financial Business Analyst, University Health Network, Canada | 2022-2023 | ● Debt compliance reporting ● Investment analysis for CAD 500M and risk-return analysis. ● Financial modeling and opportunity cost analysis for financing decision-making. ● Submit several reports to the Ministry of Finance and Ministry of Health. ● Creating Quarterly budget and forecast on adaptive. ● Cash flow forecasting and Cashflow modeling to identify free cash flow. ● Identify, investigate, and solve variances by recommending the correct course of actions ● Performance analysis, expense analysis, and General Ledger analysis. ● Preparing reports for the Finance Director, CFO, and CEO. ● Keeping continuous communication with external stakeholders for compliance purposes. || Key Responsibilities: | Financial Consultant, Estee Lauder (DECIEM), (Contractual) Canada | 2022-2022 | ● Cost development, calculation, and analysis on Microsoft 365 Dynamics. ● Identify, investigate, and solve variances. ● Create costing sheets by weighted average cost to aggregate into inventory valuation and eventually cost of goods sold. ● Assist the Inventory Team in developing and executing an SKU-level costing exercise to value inventory on Microsoft 365 Dynamics. ● Preparing for audit work, walkthrough of the costing calculation as well as the preparation of reports and other documentation. ● Assist the auditors with any cost accounting queries and walk auditor through on Microsoft 365 Dynamics. ● Ledger AnalysisxS ● , Ledger, and Trial balance reconciliation. ● Calculating the Cost of goods sold from and implement on Microsoft 365 Dynamics. ● Inventory 